# Known CRITICAL findings we intentionally accept or can't fix without
# a base-image change. Revisit on each agent-infra/sandbox upstream bump.

# --- base image upstream (enterprise-public-cn-beijing.cr.volces.com) ---
# linux_amd64_ve is a stripped Go binary shipped in the base image.
# Multiple stdlib CVEs flow from it. Upstream owns the fix.
# CVE-2025-68121 listed here because linux_amd64_ve is Go 1.17.13 stdlib;
# our own binaries are built with Go 1.25.9 and are NOT affected.
CVE-2023-24538
CVE-2023-24540
CVE-2024-24790
CVE-2025-68121

# --- Node.js (base image; needed for @anthropic-ai/claude-code) ---
CVE-2019-19919
CVE-2021-23369
CVE-2021-23383
CVE-2022-2216
CVE-2022-2900
CVE-2023-26114
CVE-2025-62718
CVE-2026-27699
CVE-2026-40175

# --- golang.org/x/crypto in projectdiscovery tools ---
# chaos/notify/asnmap depend on x/crypto v0.31; PD has not bumped upstream.
# Revisit after next PD release bundle; re-pin those three tools.
CVE-2024-45337
